{"questionId":"12237","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <strong><em>A</em></strong>, <strong><em>B</em> </strong>and <strong><em>C</em> </strong>be non-singular 2×2 matrices, <strong><em>I</em> </strong>the 2×2 identity matrix and <em>k</em> a scalar. The following statements are <strong>incorrect</strong>. For each statement, write down the correct version of the right hand side.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">(<strong><em>A</em> </strong>+ <strong><em>B</em></strong>)<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;= <strong><em>A</em></strong><sup>2</sup>&nbsp;+ 2<strong><em>AB</em> </strong>+ <strong><em>B</em></strong><sup>2</sup></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(<strong><em>A</em></strong> + <strong><em>B</em></strong>)<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;= <strong><em>A</em></strong><sup>2</sup>&nbsp;+ <strong><em>AB</em></strong> + <strong><em>BA</em></strong> + <strong><em>B</em></strong><sup>2</sup> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A2</em></strong></p>\n<p><em></em><em></em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Award&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;in parts (a) to (c) if error is correctly identified, but not corrected.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12237","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.27a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"(A + B)2 = A2 + 2AB + B2","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}